statement: M ->* N1 and M ->* N2 implies exists N3 with N1 ->* N3 and N2 ->* N3
M -> N1 and M -> N2 implies exists N3 with N1 -> N3 and N2 -> N3
Same as confluence but with typed terms
If G |- M : A and M -> N then G |- N : A
Normal forms are unique up to alpha
NbE always produces the same normal form
